<term>Second Ku Klux Klan</term> <meaning id="fs-idp18997312">unlike the secret terror group of the Reconstruction Era, the Second Ku Klux Klan was a nationwide movement that expressed racism, nativism, anti-Semitism, and anti-Catholicism</meaning>
</definition>
